The paper deals with denoising of discrete data, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The algorithm introduced in the paper, S-DUDE, is a generalization of DUDE, which is a machine learning algorithm (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the performance of S-DUDE in the context of piecewise stationary processes, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper presents preliminary experimental results, which suggests that S-DUDE can improve performance in applications where the nature of the data abruptly changes in time or space, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
